occipitocervical fusion resulted in disappearance of the soft-tissue thickening 
and normalisation of subsequent development of the dens. We conclude that the 
severity of neurological involvement at the craniovertebral junction was 
determined by soft-tissue changes, not by the type of odontoid dysplasia nor by 
subluxation. Posterior occipitocervical fusion proved to be an effective 
treatment.

