225. Plast Reconstr Surg. 1991 Nov;88(5):810-3. doi: 
10.1097/00006534-199111000-00011.

Is iliac node clearance necessary for stage II melanoma?

Zoltie N(1), Chapman P, Joss G.

Author information:
(1)Department of Plastic Surgery, West Norwich Hospital, England.

Comment in
    Plast Reconstr Surg. 1992 Sep;90(3):537-8.

In a retrospective review (1970-1983), survival following block dissection of 
the groin was compared in two groups with clinical stage II melanoma. Twenty 
patients under one surgeon had ilioinguinal (high) block dissection, and 22 
patients under another surgeon had inguinal (low) block dissection. The high 
block 5-year survival was 40 percent, and the low block 5-year survival was 35 
percent. There was no statistical difference between groups on life-table or 
log-rank test analysis. It is concluded that the extent of groin dissection has 
no effect on survival of stage II melanoma.

